---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CtaBanner from '../../components/CtaBanner.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="701am — Earned Media for Healthcare"
  description="Healthcare runs on trust, and trust is earned in the press long before the contract. Earned media for the providers, staffing firms, payers, and health-tech companies the sector decides to believe."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Industries', url: '/industries' },
    { name: 'Healthcare' },
  ]}
>

  <!-- ════ HERO ════ -->
  <section class="hero" id="top">
    <div class="hero-grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-rays" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-sun" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="hero-overline">
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
        Industries · For healthcare
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
      </p>

      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        In healthcare, the brand is the<br />promise. <em>Earn the promise.</em>
      </h1>

      <p class="hero-deck">
        Patients, hospital boards, and health systems do not buy on the brochure — they buy on the name they already trust with the stakes. <em>The organisation quoted on the shortage, the breakthrough, or the cost is the one the sector decides to believe.</em>
      </p>

      <div class="cta-cluster">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="/discovery">
          Book a sunrise call
          <span class="btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <a class="btn-link" href="#method">
          See how it works
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="cta-fine">Thirty minutes. No deck. No pitch. No charge.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ PRESS STRIP ════ -->
  <section class="press-strip" aria-label="Where the healthcare story gets told">
    <div class="press-inner">
      <p class="press-label">
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
        Where the healthcare story gets told
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
      </p>
      <div class="press-logos">
        <span class="press-logo press-condensed">BECKER'S HOSPITAL REVIEW</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-italic">Modern Healthcare</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-condensed">STAT NEWS</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-italic">Fierce Healthcare</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-roman">HealthLeaders</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 01 — THE FIRST TRUTH ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 01 · The first truth</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">Healthcare is a trust market —<br /><em>and trust is earned in print.</em></h2>
      <div class="body">
        <p class="dropcap">
          Every healthcare organisation says the same three words: quality, access, outcomes. A patient choosing care, a system choosing a vendor, a board choosing a partner — they cannot tell you apart on the spec sheet, so they fall back on the only signal that matters with stakes this high: <em>which name have I seen the sector trust.</em>
        </p>

        <div class="aphorism">The chart is read before the brochure</div>

        <p>
          That trust is not bought with a paid campaign that ends with the budget. It is built when a reporter writing about the shortage, the breakthrough, or the cost of care calls <strong>you</strong> for the number — when your chief medical officer is the named source on the story the whole sector is arguing about.
        </p>

        <p>
          The proof is in your own data right now. Outcomes for the cases everyone else avoids. Time-to-treatment in the markets no one will serve. What your clinicians say in the surveys no one publishes. Each is a story a health reporter is hunting for and <em>cannot get from your competitors.</em> Most organisations file it under compliance. The ones the sector trusts recognise it as the most valuable un-pitched story they own.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ WHO THIS IS FOR ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ — Who this is for</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">One sector. <em>Four rooms.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-center">
        <p>
          Healthcare is not one buyer — it is providers, staffing, payers, and the technology rebuilding all three. The office finds the one true sentence for each. <em>Whichever room you sit in, the work begins with your data and ends with your name in print.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="aud-grid">
        <article class="aud-card">
          <p class="aud-tag">For the provider</p>
          <h3 class="aud-h">Health Systems &amp; <em>Providers.</em></h3>
          <p class="aud-p">
            You are fighting for patient trust and board confidence in the same year margins are thinnest. We turn your outcomes — the cases you win that others won't take — into the angle that puts your CMO on the page the sector is reading.
          </p>
          <p class="aud-line">CEO · CMO · Marketing · Foundation</p>
        </article>

        <article class="aud-card">
          <p class="aud-tag">For the operator</p>
          <h3 class="aud-h">Staffing &amp; <em>Services.</em></h3>
          <p class="aud-p">
            In a market of interchangeable firms, the one quoted on the workforce shortage is the one hospitals remember. We mine your fill and retention data for the number no competitor can claim.
          </p>
          <p class="aud-line">Founder · VP Growth · Ops</p>
        </article>

        <article class="aud-card">
          <p class="aud-tag">For the builder</p>
          <h3 class="aud-h">Payers &amp; <em>Health-Tech.</em></h3>
          <p class="aud-p">
            Your category is loud and your sales cycle is long. An earned story in the trade a CIO reads becomes the proof point in every deck after. We find the claim your usage data can defend and no rival can match.
          </p>
          <p class="aud-line">Founder · CMO · Comms · Clinical</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 02 — THE LEDGER ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy ledger-section">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 02 · The ledger</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What an earned placement <em>does for a desk.</em></h2>

      <div class="ledger-grid">
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">18</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Placements earned</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">In a single quarter</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">3</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Trade-tier outlets</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">Becker's · Modern Healthcare · STAT</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">1</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Un-ignorable number</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">Pulled from the outcomes data</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ledger-prose">
        <p>
          The pattern repeats across the sector. We spend the first weeks finding the figure no competitor can claim — a shortage closed, an outcome that beats the benchmark, a cost story that contradicts the headline — and the rest placing it where the deciders already read. <em>The specialty changes. The mechanism does not.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Illustrative of the pattern. Client specifics confidential. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 03 — THE METHOD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="method">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <p class="proclamation-hinge">
        The office holds the same two articles, whatever the industry on the masthead —
      </p>

      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 03 · The method</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2 h2-dark">Two things. Done <em>without compromise.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-dark body-center">
        <p>
          We do not run your patient marketing or write your blog. We build the conditions under which a board, a system, or a patient already trusts your name before the decision. <em>The method fits on a single page, and it does not bend for the vertical.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <article class="doc">
        <header class="doc-header">
          <div class="doc-stamp">★ Tenets of the office ★</div>
          <h3 class="doc-title">The Two Articles of Earned Authority</h3>
          <p class="doc-sub">Adopted at sunrise. Held for the healthcare desk.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. i</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Find the angle inside your outcomes.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              Buried in your data is one true sentence about the future of care that no competitor can claim and no editor can refuse. <em>It is almost never the thing in your investor deck.</em> We sit with your clinical and operations teams until we find it, and then we sharpen it until it cuts.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. ii</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Place it where the sector reads.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              A claim in a press release is still a press release. We do the unglamorous work — the research, the pitch, the follow-up — until the right reporter at <em>Becker's</em> or <em>Modern Healthcare</em> runs the story. Then we do it again, until your name is the answer when the sector asks who is getting it right.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-sig">
          <p class="doc-sig-line">— 701am, est. at sunrise</p>
          <div class="doc-sig-title">Office of Earned Media</div>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-wax">7:01</div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 04 — WHAT CHANGES ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="work">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 04 · What changes</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What changes when <em>the sector trusts your name.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-center">
        <p>
          We do not sell deliverables — we change your position. <em>Here is what it is worth when the press, the board, and the patient already know who you are.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="stamp-rule">
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-time">7:01</div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="eng-grid">
        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">i.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">The outcome</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">You are the <em>name they already know.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            When a board, a system, or a patient is deciding, your name is no longer one of four on a list — it is the one they have already seen the sector trust. The decision starts in your favour.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Recognised before the first meeting</li>
            <li>Trusted where it counts most</li>
            <li>Chosen when the stakes are highest</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">ii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">The outcome</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">The deals <em>come to you.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            When your CMO is the named source on the shortage or the breakthrough, the buyers you were chasing start the conversation themselves. Earned authority turns outbound into inbound.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Inbound from buyers you pursued</li>
            <li>Shorter, warmer sales cycles</li>
            <li>A pipeline that compounds</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">iii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">The outcome</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Authority that <em>outlasts the campaign.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            A placement is not a moment — it is an asset. The story the sector cites about you keeps working in every deck, every board meeting, every recruiting call, long after the work is done.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Proof that never expires</li>
            <li>Credibility in every room</li>
            <li>A position competitors can't buy</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ WHY THE OFFICE ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ — Why the office</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">Why founders <em>choose 701am.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-center">
        <p>
          There is no shortage of agencies that promise coverage. <em>There are very few that will sit with you, find the one true thing, and stake their name on placing it.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="aud-grid">
        <article class="aud-card">
          <p class="aud-tag">Founder-led</p>
          <h3 class="aud-h">You work with <em>David.</em></h3>
          <p class="aud-p">
            Not an account manager, not an intern on a template. David sits with you himself, finds the angle, and runs the pitch — the same operator who has built and grown businesses, not just talked about them.
          </p>
          <p class="aud-line">One hour. One desk. One person accountable.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="aud-card">
          <p class="aud-tag">An operator's eye</p>
          <h3 class="aud-h">We read <em>what others miss.</em></h3>
          <p class="aud-p">
            The angle no competitor can copy is almost never in your deck. It is in the operations and outcomes data most agencies never think to read — and finding it is the whole game.
          </p>
          <p class="aud-line">The story hiding in your own numbers.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="aud-card">
          <p class="aud-tag">Nothing invented</p>
          <h3 class="aud-h">Only what is <em>true.</em></h3>
          <p class="aud-p">
            We never fabricate a number, a quote, or a claim. Earned authority that cannot survive a fact-check is not authority — it is a liability. Everything we place is real, and that is exactly why it lands.
          </p>
          <p class="aud-line">No invented stats. Ever.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ FOUNDER NOTE ════ -->
  <section class="founder-note">
    <div class="founder-inner reveal">
      <p class="founder-eyebrow">
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
        A note from the office
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
      </p>
      <blockquote class="founder-quote">
        There are a thousand organisations promising better care. There are perhaps a handful who can get a reporter to call them first when the sector's biggest question is being written. <em>We are built for the second problem.</em> If that is the one keeping you up, the sunrise call is free.
      </blockquote>
      <p class="founder-sig">
        <span class="founder-name">— David</span>
        <span class="founder-time">at 7:01</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § — FROM THE FIELD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ — In their words</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What people say <em>about David.</em></h2>

      <div class="field-grid">
        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            David is a key piece to company growth. His SEO insights are next level. He is always on top of the new trends that impact website performance and takes initiative. But above that, David is a great leader and great person to work with!
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Alison Tobin</span>
            <span class="field-role">Insurance Editor</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            I have never learned so much from someone I worked with. He was always an inspiration to me. He's the hardest worker I have ever met. No idea how he finds the time to accomplish all he does in a day. Couldn't have more respect for him.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Sara Routhier</span>
            <span class="field-role">Senior Director of Content at Quote.com</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            David's expertise in SEO is incredible. He has the ability to jump between SEO strategies and tactics to drive substantial growth while managing and leading high performance teams. He's an impactful (and essential) person to have on your growth team!
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Meredith Kokos</span>
            <span class="field-role">AI-Driven SVP of Growth | Scaling PE &amp; VC-Backed B2C/DTC &amp; B2B Companies</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Recommendations from people who have worked with David. Words unchanged. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ CTA ════ -->
  <CtaBanner
    eyebrow="The work begins at 7:01"
    heading="Ready to be the name <em>the sector trusts?</em>"
    body="Thirty minutes. We listen, find the angle hiding in your outcomes data, and tell you straight whether we can make your organisation impossible for the sector to ignore."
    primaryLabel="Book a sunrise call"
    primaryHref="/discovery"
    secondaryLabel="Or read the field manual"
    secondaryHref="/legend-maker"
  />

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ─────── WHO THIS IS FOR — buyer-segment cards (optional) ─────── */
  .aud-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .aud-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5));
    position: relative;
  }
  .aud-card + .aud-card { border-left: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  .aud-tag {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
  }
  .aud-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "dlig" 1;
    font-size: var(--f4-size);
    line-height: 1.1;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .aud-h em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--claret); }
  .aud-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .aud-p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); }
  .aud-line {
    margin: 0;
    padding-top: var(--x4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ─────── ENGAGEMENTS — mirrors the index "offers" three-up ─────── */
  .eng-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .eng-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5));
    position: relative;
  }
  .eng-card + .eng-card { border-left: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  .eng-num {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: var(--f3-size);
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-variant-numeric: oldstyle-nums;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-tier {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "dlig" 1;
    font-size: var(--f4-size);
    line-height: 1.12;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .eng-h em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--claret); }
  .eng-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .eng-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--x4) 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .eng-list li {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    padding: var(--x5) 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--x4);
    counter-increment: eng;
  }
  .eng-list { counter-reset: eng; }
  .eng-list li::before {
    content: counter(eng, lower-roman) ".";
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-size: 12px;
    min-width: 1.4em;
  }

  /* ─────── FROM THE FIELD — mirrors the index testimonial cards ─────── */
  .field-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--x3);
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
  }
  .field-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--claret);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5)) var(--x2);
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .field-mark {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    line-height: 0.5;
    height: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--claret);
  }
  .field-quote {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
    flex: 1;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .field-by {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-top: var(--x4);
  }
  .field-name {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
